File: Officials have recommended that people should ensure that they wash their hands using soap for 20 seconds. JOHANNESBURG - Ensuring that you properly wash your hands is one of the ways to stop the spread of viruses and germs. As the coronavirus (COVID-19) continues to spread throughout the world, health officials recommend that people should wash their hands, regularly, using soap for 20 seconds. However, sometimes you may not have access to water or soap and that is why it is important to always have a hand sanitiser with you. READ: 8 tips on what to tell your kids about coronavirus Due to an increase in the number of reported coronavirus cases, there has been a spike in hand sanitiser sales around the country. To help avoid a situation where sanitisers are sold-out, Dischem is encouraging consumers to make their own hand sanitisers. During an interview on Breakfast with Martin Bester, head of Dischem clinics Lizeth Kruger, said making your own hand sanitiser is really simple. Ingredients to make your own hand sanitizer:  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.